    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n(N)vim displays line feed characters in file names as `^@` (null) due to a implementation detail, and not [the correct caret notation of `^J`](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASCII#Control_code_table). Ideally, Nvim does not expose this implementation detail, and line feeds are displayed as the correct code point.\n\nCurrent behavior (`nvim $'/tmp/newline\\nfile'`):\n\n<img width=\"865\" height=\"561\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/797af255-da87-41ed-9146-953a23b1cdde\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShow `\\n` in the UI as `^J` (or `<0a>` with `:set display+=uhex`).\n\nWas closed as not planned by Vim (https://github.com/vim/vim/issues/20060).\n\n[Discussed on Matrix here](https://matrix.to/#/!cylwlNXSwagQmZSkzs:matrix.org/$okHznKGuXJWspLWA7Pu6y-KqTMkoN7GmMN4Fxz_ll38?via=mozilla.org&via=matrix.org&via=gitter.im).",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-25T22:21:01Z",
