        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> It will require tracking whether every NL byte is an actual NL or a Nul throughout it's lifecycle.\n\nI don't believe we actually need to track every NUL byte; we just need to change how we display buffer names. For all buffer names, `^@` should be `^J`. Everywhere else, we don't make any changes. No actual changes to the data should be needed. Correct me if I'm wrong and it's more complicated than that.\n\n> Nul in a filename\n\nIt's not just rare, it's not possible (under Unix).",
            "created_at": "2026-04-25T23:08:04Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39408#issuecomment-4320771439",
