        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> What exactly is \"display buffer names\"?\n\nIn places where a buffer name is written to the UI, and you know it's a buffer name. Places like the statusline, `:ls`, `'title'`, quickfix window names, etc.\n\n> If you use a function to get a buffer name, and then display it in a UI element, is that not \"display buffer names\"?\n\nYeah, there might be some cases where you can't reason about whether something is a buffer name or not, and then you'd need to fall back to displaying `^@`. But surely >95% of cases won't be arbitrary like that. I don't expect it to come up very often.\n",
