        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'm sure there are ways to go about this, but I do agree that they would be `complexity:high`. Ideally this could be reconsidered eventually but I agree it's probably not worth the effort right now.\n\nAnyway, if the plan isn't the change this behavior, that at least makes handling newlines in filenames for a netrw replacement really easy. You just replace `\\n` with `\\0` (and vice versa when going the other direction) and it \"just works\".",
